name: Microsoft HealthVault
title: Awesome!
text: Works great on iPhone 5 AND with OpenID - I just created my Account with no issues! Sweet app - lets me carry all my Health Information with me offline. And this is a full featured NATIVE iOS app, fast and responsive -- not a web app. Also - your phone already has a pin code, so use it. Some reviewers here appear biased...

name: FitnessSyncer
title: Broken: needs to be updated
text:
Upon initial install under previous version of iOS, this app seemed just thing needed to sync my Apple Health information to Fitbit, so I purchased the Pro plan and away it synced.

Upon updating both my iPhone, and reinstalling the app for good measure, the app presents me with a blank, black screen before dying after about 30s. Background syncing wasn't happening, instead I was being prompted via notification to launch and manually sync.

The UI isn't that great but is functional. 

CONCLUSION: fix the app.

name: My Medical
title: MD
text: A complete disappointment. Simply a word document with broad categories and no defined structure that would be acceptable ti any clinician.

name: Healthspek - Personal Health Record & Family Health Record - Complete Medical Record
title: Michael Reardon MD
text:
I was so pleased to find this medical app today. I love the layout, ease of use and attention to detail. It reminds me of google health which was discontinued. This app is in many ways better than google health which I felt was the best available a few years ago.
      If you use this app then please give them your input. These guys are into CQI (continuous quality improvement) and they always want to make it better.
        I love the way you can email your entire record. I can see this app allowing download of lab results etc in the future.

name: Medfusion Plus
title: Top class
text: This is a top app. The high-quality app is used to maintain and access all your family's health data in one place. It is a really good one.

name: higi
title: Logging in
text: I'm having issues logging back in. Username and password will let me log in at the station but refuses on the the app.

name: Sharecare
title: False advertising
text: Reading the book "Age Proof" by the co-creators of this app and was advised to download Sharecare, a supposedly free app that will be helpful in tracking some of the data needed for accurate health diagnostics. Now the app wants a verification code from my health insurer or employer? Nowhere in the book does it state that one would be needed. Total waste of my time.

name: Aetna Mobile
title: They mean it when they say search!!
text: Are you serious?!?!? You expect someone to look through 500 names? Why type in an individual name if I then have to scan through 500 of them to find that Dr? Come on Aetna! Disappointing! Great idea - just not ready for prime time!

name: Kaiser Permanente
title: Map feature not useful
text:
I have not tried to login yet but the map feature made me wonder if it is worth even trying. It took a couple of minutes for the app to become minimally responsive.

One major criticism of the map filter is that it does not list Kaiser's Urgent Care facilities. The Map Search does not pick up keywords so searching for 'urgent' sent me to Urgench, Uzbekistan! 

The filter allows one to choose Amenities or Other Services but does not give a second menu to further refine a search. 

Their website locator is not great but is better than this so no reason for this app to waste space on my phone.

name: myCigna
title: Lots of room for improvement
text:
Need finger print login, like the banking APPS. Information need better organization. You can see you medical card, but just a few numbers not a nice graphical card that resembles the printed card you receive.

Every time one visits a medical  office they are asked for the medical card. Need to be able to supply this via the app.

I just started using the APP and it apparent there is a lot of room for improvement.

name: Blue Shield of California
title: Doesn't work
text: Can't login to the app. Yes, I'm using the correct username and password, but it gives me an error saying "invalid credentials". Blue Shield really needs to get their act together, not just regarding this app.

name: MyHumana
title: Terrible service
text: Can't get app to work. Called about new prescription yesterday and girl tried to give me 90 day supply of antibiotic that had 6 weeks prior non refillable! Then tried to give me 90 day prescription of new one!! I am at dr office and they are trying to get me 3 referrals. Took half hour for them to get just one referral and it was very difficult. I am sitting in front of nurse making call and she is having hard time getting them to understand anything!! They are not very well trained on other end apparently! I am very disappointed in Humana!

name: Anthem Anywhere
title: Location aware severely limits app
text: Want to find that urgent care facility nearby, great, the app will direct you to the nearest facility. Want find an urgent care facility for a family member injured on a trip out of the area, useless, because the app can only be used to find a nearby facility. You cannot enter an alternative location to search.

name: Capital BlueCross Virtual Care
title: Horrible
text: All I need was a prescription my pharmacy never received my prescription the customer support was as clueless as my myself! Horrible Experience! This app is totally pointless if a minor prescription can’t  be faxed or called in correctly! The doctor just abruptly ended the video chat! Horrible App!!!
